---
year: 4
title: Mathematics Dissertation
course-acronym: mathdiss
pinned: true
learn: false
---

- Not available for Y4 MMath students as it is compulsory for MMath Students in Year 5.
- Opportunity to research a subject in depth (using LaTeX) under the guidance of an experienced mathematician.
- Masters level difficulty, and a good dissertation may be part of a monograph or a published paper in a refereed journal.
- 10 hours of project supervision, 8 hours of programme level learning and teaching, 382 hours of directed and independent learning.
- The coursework assessment will be based 20% on oral presentation and 80% on written report.
